kkasperczyk/ai-portfolio-companion/apps/api/src/routes/portfolio.ts`\n- `/Users/leszekkasperczyk/ai-portfolio-companion/apps/api/src/routes/insights.ts`\n- `/Users/leszekkasperczyk/ai-portfolio-companion/apps/api/src/routes/chat.ts`\n\n## Run instructions\n\n```bash\ncd apps/api\nnpm install\nnpm run dev\n```\n\nThe server starts on `http://localhost:3000`.\n\n## Test instructions\n\n```bash\n# Health check\ncurl http://localhost:3000/health\n\n# Portfolio summary with computed metrics\ncurl http://localhost:3000/api/portfolio\n\n# AI insights array\ncurl http://localhost:3000/api/insights\n\n# Streaming chat (SSE — watch words arrive progressively, ends with [DONE])\ncurl -N -X POST http://localhost:3000/api/chat/stream \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\"message\": \"How is my portfolio?\"}'\n```\n\n## Assumptions\n\n1. **`tsx` used as the dev runner instead of `ts-node`** — `tsx` is already installed and works with TypeScript 6. `ts-node` is listed in devDependencies for spec compliance but the `dev` script uses `tsx` since `ts-node` has known issues with TS 6's module resolution defaults.\n\n2. **Express 5 streaming workaround** — Express 5's `express.json()` middleware buffers the incoming request body, which prevents SSE chunks from flushing. The `/api/chat` router is registered before `express.json()` in `index.ts` to avoid this. The trade-off is that `req.body` is not parsed on the chat route, which is acceptable because the mock response is hardcoded and does not use the request body.\n\n3. **`dailyChange` is a hardcoded mock percentage** (`1.8`) — consistent across portfolio and insights, no randomness to keep responses stable.\n\n4. **CORS allows `http://localhost:8100`** — the Ionic default dev port. The frontend may also run on `http://localhost:4200` (Angular CLI default) but `8100` matches the task spec exactly.\n\n5. **`src/utils` directory not created** — the task brief lists it as optional structure. There is no shared utility logic warranting it in the current scope."}
