[2026-03-28T16:05:53Z] {"session_id":"3cc1157d-dcbc-44df-bbba-ed7274e81f0f","transcript_path":"/Users/leszekkasperczyk/.claude/projects/-Users-leszekkasperczyk-ai-portfolio-companion/3cc1157d-dcbc-44df-bbba-ed7274e81f0f.jsonl","cwd":"/Users/leszekkasperczyk/ai-portfolio-companion","permission_mode":"acceptEdits","agent_id":"ab7c5782491c4f840","agent_type":"frontend","hook_event_name":"SubagentStop","stop_hook_active":false,"agent_transcript_path":"/Users/leszekkasperczyk/.claude/projects/-Users-leszekkasperczyk-ai-portfolio-companion/3cc1157d-dcbc-44df-bbba-ed7274e81f0f/subagents/agent-ab7c5782491c4f840.jsonl","last_assistant_message":"The implementation is complete and verified. Here is the required structured response.\n\n---\n\n## Plan\n\nI read all the relevant docs and existing source files first, then called advisor before writing any code. The implementation plan was:\n\n1. Replace the stub `DashboardPage` class with a full component that fetches data via `forkJoin`, manages `loading`/`error`/data state, and computes derived values (daily change percent, per-holding gain/loss) in the class.\n2. Replace the stub template with three conditional sections: loading spinner, error + retry button, and the data view (summary card, holdings list, insights section) plus a pull-to-refresh.\n3. Create a minimal SCSS file for layout and positive/negative color classes.\n\n---\n\n## Files changed\n\n- `/Users/leszekkasperczyk/ai-portfolio-companion/apps/mobile/src/app/features/dashboard/dashboard.page.ts` — full component implementation\n- `/Users/leszekkasperczyk/ai-portfolio-companion/apps/mobile/src/app/features/dashboard/dashboard.page.html` — full template\n- `/Users/leszekkasperczyk/ai-portfolio-companion/apps/mobile/src/app/features/dashboard/dashboard.page.scss` — new file, layout and color utilities\n\nNo other files were touched.\n\n---\n\n## Behavior summary\n\n**Loading state.** When the component initializes (or retry is pressed), `loading` is set to `true` and `error` is cleared. A centered `IonSpinner` with a \"Loading portfolio...\" label is shown. The data sections are hidden.\n\n**Error state.** If the `forkJoin` fails, `error` is set to a human-readable message and `loading` is cleared. The spinner is replaced by the error message and a \"Retry\" `IonButton` that calls `loadData()` again.\n\n**Data state.** On success, three sections render:\n\n- **Portfolio Summary card** — total value (USD currency pipe), daily change in dollars and percent (both with explicit `+`/`-` sign, colored green/red via CSS class), total gain/loss in dollars with sign and color.\n- **Holdings card** — `IonList` with one `IonItem` per holding showing: symbol (bold), name, quantity and current price per share. The right slot shows the per-holding gain/loss (`(currentPrice - avgCostBasis) * quantity`) in USD with sign and color.\n- **AI Insights card** — each insight string rendered as a paragraph in its own bordered row. Falls back to \"No insights available.\" if the array is empty.\n\n**Pull-to-refresh.** An `IonRefresher` at the top of `IonContent` calls `loadData($event)` and completes the spinner whether the fetch succeeds or fails.\n\n---\n\n## Test instructions\n\n1. Start the backend: `cd /Users/leszekkasperczyk/ai-portfolio-companion/apps/api && npm run dev` (or equivalent). Confirm it serves on `http://localhost:3000`.\n2. Start the mobile app: `cd /Users/leszekkasperczyk/ai-portfolio-companion/apps/mobile && npx ionic serve`.\n3. Open `http://localhost:8100` in a browser (or run in the iOS simulator via `npx ionic capacitor run ios`).\n4. Navigate to the Dashboard tab.\n5. Verify the spinner appears briefly, then disappears and shows: total value, daily change with sign and %, total gain/loss with sign, a list of holdings each with symbol/name/price/quantity/gain-loss, and AI insights.\n6. To test error state: stop the backend and reload the page. The error message and \"Retry\" button should appear. Restart the backend, press \"Retry\", and data should load.\n7. To test pull-to-refresh: pull down from the top of the content area. The refresher spinner should appear and data should reload.\n\n---\n\n## Assumptions\n\n- The `dailyChange` field in `PortfolioSummary` is a dollar amount, not a fraction. The daily change percentage is computed as `dailyChange / (totalValue - dailyChange) * 100`.\n- Per-holding gain/loss is computed as `(currentPrice - avgCostBasis) * quantity`. The model does not include a `totalGainLoss` per holding, so this is derived in the component.\n- The `Insight` type (`string`) means each element is rendered directly as text -- no further parsing.\n- The bundle-size budget warning in the build output is pre-existing (Ionic's own weight) and is not caused by this change."}
